title: Print, "Tradecard, Frederick Crace and Son", ca. 1837
inscribed: Inscribed on plate, center: Crace and Son / House Painters & Decorators / TO THE QUEEN / 14, Wigmore Street / Cavendish Square.
creditline: Museum purchase through gift of Mrs. John Innes Kane
description: Trade card with center inscription flanked by two female figures on left and right. Upper center, coat  of arms.
